claim.claim-text:
1. An anti-bacterial composition for plants comprising:
garlic oil;
cinnamon oil;
thyme oil;
oleic acid; and
dimethyl sulfoxide.

6. A method of treating an infected plant comprising the steps of:
forming at least one hole in the phloem of the plant;
injecting a therapeutic amount of a compound comprising garlic oil; cinnamon oil; thyme oil; oleic acid; and dimethyl sulfoxide;
sealing the at least one hole.

13. An anti-bacterial composition for plants comprising:
wherein garlic oil is present in an amount of 20% by weight;
cinnamon oil is present in an amount of 50% by weight;
thyme oil is present in an amount of 20% by weight;
oleic acid is present in an amount of 9.85% by weight; and
dimethyl sulfoxide is present in an amount of from 0.15% by weight, the weights based on a total weight of the composition.
